<p>I am deeply honored that the venerable German firm of Rowohlt will publish two books of mine in late November. One is <em>Die Welt nach Wagner</em>, a translation of <em>Wagnerism</em> by GÃ¼nter Kotzor and Gloria Buschor-Kotzor. The other is a translation of my second book, <em>Listen to This</em>, by Dieter Fuchs. My German is far from perfect, but it is good enough to be able to appreciate the extraordinary, quasi-<em>Ã¼bermenschlich</em> efforts on the part of the translators, who faced some fairly intractable problems not only with my prose but with the mÃ©lange of sources on which I drew. Meine Dankbarkeit ist riesengroÃ und grenzenlos.</p>
