<p>Justin Brown, the general music director in Karlsruhe, is exiting his position after a remarkably rich tenure. He tells me that he chose the Choral Fantasy for his farewell project because of &quot;the optimism embedded in its fan-shaped construction&quot;: solo piano leading to massed instruments and then to voices. Ninety-five performers participated, but there were never more than twenty on stage at once. More details <a href="http://www.staatstheater.karlsruhe.de/programm/info/3177/">here</a>.</p>
